			<h2 class="mb0 text-primary">Roster Updates</h2>
			<span class="update-meta">Jan. 20th, 2016</span>
			<p class="lead text-justify">Our goal is to simplify your gaming life and help you connect with great players.  Today we are happy to introduce Game Roster, which will formally replace Paid 2 Play as the name of our site and provide new features that will help you organize all your clan events, raids, and competitions.</p>

			<p class="lead text-justify">You can now set up private game events and instantly know who is on each game's interactive roster.  In addition, you will now be able to share public events and your availability on social media and will find more tools that improve group communication and your ability to find ideal players and games.  A full recap of the changes is as follows:</p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Create Private Event Rosters</strong> &ndash; create game event rosters that are only visible to invited players. </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Game Event Invites</strong> &ndash; send invites to all your friends even if they are not yet using the site.  </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Create Public Games</strong> &ndash; start a public game and ask others to join that meet your PSA and cancelation rate preferences.</p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Social Media</strong> &ndash; post game events or your availability to join players on Facebook and Twitter. </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Join Public Games</strong> &ndash; lists public games with new stats like play type (serious/casual), roster size, and host age. </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>My Events</strong> &ndash; see all your game invites and interactive rosters for your confirmed private and public game events. </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Favorites</strong> &ndash; add players and quickly access favorites for invites and messages.  </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Age Options</strong> &ndash; share your age to help find ideal players and titles. Set your preference on the <%= link_to "Edit Profile", edit_profile_path %> page.  </p>

			<p class="lead"><strong>Group Messaging</strong> &ndash; send messages to the entire team.  Your email information stays private.  </p>

		</section>
