		<section class="update">
			<h2 class="mb0 text-primary">Major Updates</h2>
			<span class="update-meta">Nov. 9th, 2015</span>
			<p class="lead">We have a number of major updates to the site to share today. </p>

			<h3>Goodbye Confusing Jargon</h3>
			<p class="lead text-justify">We are transitioning away from some confusing jargon and renaming Contracts and Bounties as Players Available and Join Game, respectively, while referring to all activities as Events.  You can post either type of event with the Post button. All our games are now supported whether you are looking for a player or offering your availability. </p>

			<h3>Donations</h3>
			<p class="lead text-justify">We are transitioning to a donation-based system that will encourage and track user generosity.  With this transition we will allow users of ALL ages to accept donations that reward good game play and behavior.  Users can collect donations on their profile page and list suggested donations on events.  Users can also list their willingness to offer a donation when they are looking for a player. </p>

			<p class="lead text-justify">Users are not obligated to donate but being more generous will help attract other players and may influence an Approval rating.  Furthermore, we will now be tracking and reporting generosity using a Generosity rating.  Donations strengthen the Game Mercenaries community and those supporters will be recognized and reported on a newly created leaderboard. </p>

			<h3>No More Fees</h3>
			<p class="lead text-justify">We are eliminating our $0.99 transaction fee so that the entire donation goes to the mercenary.   This site is about you the gamer and we want to give you the best shot at getting some money doing what you love. </p>

			<h3>Honest Ratings</h3>
			<p class="lead text-justify">In an effort to encourage more honest feedback we are making ratings anonymous and allowing users to rerate players on their Rate & Block players page.  You ratings will be included in a users average rating but not disclosed.  Your qualitative rating/review comments will show up on a user’s page but will NOT be attributed to your profile. </p>


			<p class="lead text-justify">More information can be found on our updated FAQ and How To pages.  As always, our goal is to help connect gamers, reward good players, and encourage good behavior. </p>


		</section>
